  "system": {
    "description": "<p>You can spend <strong>1 AP</strong> and <strong>1 MP</strong> to create your own <strong>Druid</strong> <strong>Domain</strong> that includes small plant life, sand, shallow water, or other naturally occurring features.</p><p>You create up to <strong>8 Domain Spaces</strong> along the ground or walls. The first Domain Space must be within 1 Space of you, and each additional Domain Space must be adjacent to another Domain Space.</p><p><strong>Domain Spaces:</strong> The area is considered to be <strong>Difficult</strong> <strong>Terrain</strong> for creatures of your choice, and when you cast a Spell, you can do so as if you were standing in any Space within your Domain.</p><p><strong>Losing Domain Spaces:</strong> A Domain Space also disappears if you end your turn farther than 15 Spaces away from it or you die.</p><p></p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Domain Actions</span></strong></span></p><p>While you have Domain Spaces, you can take any of the following Domain Actions:</p><ul><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.ZTngnNqIQrkgq8a7]{Nature’s Grasp}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.z8ioBDbxkTfw1QK9]{Wild Growth}</p></li></ul>",
